WEBVTT

00:00:00.033 --> 00:00:04.199
[Dreams]

00:00:11.210 --> 00:00:13.172
Will the article be published?

00:00:13.172 --> 00:00:15.586
No, I've resolved the issue.

00:00:15.586 --> 00:00:17.315
But how?

00:00:24.124 --> 00:00:25.704
GM?

00:00:32.844 --> 00:00:34.906
Excuse me.

00:00:36.780 --> 00:00:41.103
Please don't be so nervous, President Makita.

00:00:41.103 --> 00:00:45.823
I've brought you good news.

00:00:45.823 --> 00:00:47.341
What is it?

00:00:48.085 --> 00:00:53.764
General Manager Sakurazaki
will be dismissed by month's end.

00:00:58.053 --> 00:01:02.047
Therefore, President Makita.

00:01:02.047 --> 00:01:06.318
I ask that you be our interim GM.

00:01:39.870 --> 00:01:42.981
Was it to retract the article
about your brother?

00:01:53.264 --> 00:01:56.060
I've put together a plan
and materials for the future.

00:01:57.744 --> 00:01:59.956
Why are you agreeing to this?

00:02:01.903 --> 00:02:03.559
GM!

00:02:10.805 --> 00:02:16.031
I always assumed
the Dreams were a team of lazy individuals.

00:02:17.823 --> 00:02:19.621
But I was wrong.

00:02:20.956 --> 00:02:23.967
You claw your way towards victory,

00:02:24.899 --> 00:02:27.533
and remain positive in the face of adversity.

00:02:29.214 --> 00:02:30.737
President Makita.

00:02:35.029 --> 00:02:36.743
I was glad to be proven wrong.

00:02:40.373 --> 00:02:44.907
I entrust the role of interim GM to you.

00:02:45.818 --> 00:02:47.379
I can't.

00:02:48.479 --> 00:02:50.839
You are our shining hope.

00:02:50.839 --> 00:02:53.711
This was an order from President Negishi.

00:02:53.711 --> 00:02:55.360
And...

00:02:59.124 --> 00:03:01.326
it is my final wish to the team.

00:03:05.842 --> 00:03:07.423
That can't be true.

00:03:07.423 --> 00:03:09.878
I know you want to win.

00:03:11.583 --> 00:03:14.322
Are we not a team?

00:03:14.322 --> 00:03:17.150
Let's get through this, together.

00:03:20.652 --> 00:03:22.421
GM!

00:03:22.421 --> 00:03:24.399
I'm not the GM anymore.

00:03:26.143 --> 00:03:27.825
Why?

00:03:28.933 --> 00:03:31.715
Why can't you ask for our help?

00:03:32.276 --> 00:03:35.226
Do you not trust us?

00:03:39.339 --> 00:03:43.990
I was guaranteed two years of my salary.

00:03:45.101 --> 00:03:47.303
So what?

00:03:47.303 --> 00:03:48.699
President Makita.

00:03:51.131 --> 00:03:53.929
I have no attachment to the team.

00:03:55.111 --> 00:03:57.289
Nor do I have any interest in baseball.

00:03:58.626 --> 00:04:00.508
I believe I've accomplished enough.

00:04:03.968 --> 00:04:05.896
Is that how you really feel?

00:04:08.824 --> 00:04:11.371
Do you truly feel well accomplished?

00:04:13.041 --> 00:04:14.366
Of course.

00:04:20.873 --> 00:04:22.432
I understand.

00:04:24.644 --> 00:04:27.865
It's not just the Dreams who need to change.

00:04:29.420 --> 00:04:31.906
You need to change yourself as well.

00:04:37.464 --> 00:04:39.874
Thank you for everything.

00:04:50.190 --> 00:04:54.481
Your renowned colleague, Mr. Sakurazaki,

00:04:54.481 --> 00:04:59.405
will be leaving at the end of this month.

00:04:59.405 --> 00:05:01.279
What happened?

00:05:02.477 --> 00:05:06.509
He chose to step down of his own accord.

00:05:07.678 --> 00:05:12.563
The GM negotiated unfairly with our catcher.

00:05:12.563 --> 00:05:15.415
He damaged the team's image.

00:05:15.415 --> 00:05:20.322
He even took advantage of his position
to hire his brother.

00:05:21.984 --> 00:05:25.569
I believe his dismissal is entirely deserved.

00:05:25.569 --> 00:05:28.342
Please strive to fill the void
left by Mr. Sakurazaki.

00:05:28.342 --> 00:05:30.001
Woah, woah, woah!

00:05:30.001 --> 00:05:31.154
Let go of me!

00:05:31.154 --> 00:05:33.337
There wasn't any foul play to speak of!

00:05:33.337 --> 00:05:36.660
I understand, but not now.

00:05:36.660 --> 00:05:39.508
If we don't speak up, the GM will be...

00:05:42.888 --> 00:05:46.950
We will continue to support the Dreams
in their endeavors.

00:06:01.926 --> 00:06:04.375
Have I made myself clear?

00:06:06.701 --> 00:06:08.939
To survive in an organization,

00:06:08.939 --> 00:06:13.143
no one can stick to their beliefs.

00:06:15.210 --> 00:06:19.367
I wish you all the best, Interim GM.

00:06:49.927 --> 00:06:51.106
Oh...

00:06:55.678 --> 00:06:59.237
Let me in on your secret plan, GM.

00:06:59.237 --> 00:07:02.865
You'll come back with a real bang, right?

00:07:02.865 --> 00:07:04.299
Right?

00:07:04.299 --> 00:07:07.561
My salary has been guaranteed.
I won't be coming back.

00:07:07.561 --> 00:07:10.608
You're only in it for the money?

00:07:11.283 --> 00:07:12.555
Of course.

00:07:12.555 --> 00:07:15.162
No, I don't believe it.

00:07:15.162 --> 00:07:17.341
You clearly have passion.

00:07:17.341 --> 00:07:20.168
Everyone here has been influenced by it.

00:07:21.349 --> 00:07:26.556
Hard work is rewarded, right?
I learned that from you.

00:07:27.423 --> 00:07:29.738
I've never been rewarded.

00:07:30.406 --> 00:07:31.808
Not once.

00:07:31.808 --> 00:07:34.317
You've led plenty of teams to victory!

00:07:34.317 --> 00:07:36.651
And they've all been disbanded.

00:07:42.177 --> 00:07:46.870
I hurt the players' pride
and destroyed the team.

00:07:47.564 --> 00:07:49.958
If I were President Negishi,

00:07:49.958 --> 00:07:52.341
I would consider firing the GM as well.

00:07:53.300 --> 00:07:54.711
No, but...

00:08:00.546 --> 00:08:01.719
Hey.

00:08:01.719 --> 00:08:03.318
GM.

00:08:03.318 --> 00:08:04.662
Hey!

00:08:07.586 --> 00:08:08.975
Thank you.

00:08:12.020 --> 00:08:14.539
I still believe in you, okay?

00:08:36.685 --> 00:08:40.790
Please publish the article as scheduled.

00:08:40.790 --> 00:08:44.263
Yes. Of course.

00:08:51.665 --> 00:08:54.669
[Dreams GM, hired his jobless brother?]
Seriously?

00:08:54.669 --> 00:08:56.732
They published the article anyway!

00:08:56.732 --> 00:08:57.826
What? What's wrong?

00:08:57.826 --> 00:08:59.990
- See?
- Unbelievable.

00:08:59.990 --> 00:09:01.320
What an absolute scumbag.

00:09:01.320 --> 00:09:03.091
Prez, could I have a minute?

00:09:03.091 --> 00:09:07.690
Shirasaki and Kato
have requested to withdraw their contracts.

00:09:07.690 --> 00:09:09.917
See? I knew it.

00:09:09.917 --> 00:09:12.128
They said they can't trust a negotiation

00:09:12.128 --> 00:09:15.006
given by an analyst
we let in through connections.

00:09:15.006 --> 00:09:16.918
They're quick.

00:09:16.918 --> 00:09:20.731
I denied any foul play,
but they wouldn't listen.

00:09:20.731 --> 00:09:24.000
I'm going to go renegotiate.

00:09:24.000 --> 00:09:25.202
We're counting on you.

00:09:25.202 --> 00:09:27.512
- Good luck.
- Alright, it's a go! Go!

00:09:27.512 --> 00:09:29.639
- Before I go.
- What? What's wrong?

00:09:29.639 --> 00:09:32.219
Alright!

00:09:32.219 --> 00:09:34.319
Huzzah! Huzzah!

00:09:34.319 --> 00:09:36.147
- Miyahara!
- That's right!

00:09:36.147 --> 00:09:38.278
Go, go, Miyahara!

00:09:38.278 --> 00:09:41.194
Go, go, Miyahara!

00:09:50.564 --> 00:09:53.395
Are you really leaving the Dreams?

00:09:58.952 --> 00:10:02.700
If it's to protect me, don't.

00:10:04.163 --> 00:10:06.993
You don't need any more protecting.

00:10:09.849 --> 00:10:14.222
This is my problem to deal with.

00:10:19.064 --> 00:10:22.550
You joined the Dreams fair and square.

00:10:29.914 --> 00:10:32.768
All you have to do is prove yourself.

00:10:33.818 --> 00:10:36.004
I know.

00:10:37.064 --> 00:10:38.719
But...

00:10:41.047 --> 00:10:43.525
Why are you always like this?

00:10:45.780 --> 00:10:47.983
Are you sure, Jun?

00:10:47.983 --> 00:10:52.236
I no longer deserve to be happy.

00:10:58.311 --> 00:11:00.721
You can't bear it anymore, can you?

00:11:10.799 --> 00:11:13.150
Dinner's ready.
[Risa]

00:11:13.150 --> 00:11:14.595
Huh?

00:11:14.595 --> 00:11:16.271
Hey, aren't you going to eat?

00:11:16.271 --> 00:11:21.353
I made omelette rice today.

00:11:21.353 --> 00:11:22.819
No, not hungry.

00:11:22.819 --> 00:11:24.665
Huh? Why?

00:11:24.665 --> 00:11:26.610
Oh no.

00:11:26.610 --> 00:11:29.130
Did you get fired?

00:11:29.130 --> 00:11:32.024
You're so insensitive.

00:11:32.024 --> 00:11:34.161
Our finances are in trouble.
What should we do?

00:11:34.161 --> 00:11:35.932
I'm not the one who got fired.

00:11:35.932 --> 00:11:37.893
Oh, I see.

00:11:37.893 --> 00:11:40.367
So it was that guy. He got fired?

00:11:40.367 --> 00:11:44.113
Well, I worried for nothing.

00:11:45.538 --> 00:11:48.528
If you're so worried, get a job.

00:11:48.528 --> 00:11:50.548
Come on, let's just eat.

00:11:50.548 --> 00:11:52.307
Here, dinner's ready.

00:12:01.143 --> 00:12:03.366
This is Makita, speaking.

00:12:03.366 --> 00:12:05.186
President Makita.

00:12:05.186 --> 00:12:07.645
Please let me handle the salary negotiations.

00:12:07.645 --> 00:12:09.418
What?

00:12:09.418 --> 00:12:13.602
I'll re-explain our criteria to all players.

00:12:14.301 --> 00:12:19.066
You'll be at an intense disadvantage.

00:12:19.066 --> 00:12:21.793
That's precisely why I wish to do this.

00:12:23.320 --> 00:12:25.381
For the sake of the team.

00:12:27.214 --> 00:12:28.977
And for my brother.

00:12:35.091 --> 00:12:37.869
I will officially explain the GM's scandal,

00:12:37.869 --> 00:12:41.030
and his dismissal early next week.

00:12:41.030 --> 00:12:43.208
He will bear all the responsibility.

00:12:43.208 --> 00:12:45.777
And to free our poor, unfortunate players,

00:12:45.777 --> 00:12:49.254
I will announce the team be disbanded.

00:12:49.254 --> 00:12:51.213
Do you know what this is?

00:12:54.645 --> 00:12:58.346
A daifuku, I believe.

00:12:59.039 --> 00:13:03.720
And what is it wrapped in?

00:13:08.871 --> 00:13:11.960
Mochi, sir.

00:13:11.960 --> 00:13:14.839
Excellent. Yes, this is mochi.

00:13:17.494 --> 00:13:18.910
Give it a try.

00:13:24.467 --> 00:13:26.251
Thank you.

00:13:33.688 --> 00:13:35.695
How is it? Good?

00:13:35.695 --> 00:13:37.245
Yes. It's delicious.

00:13:37.245 --> 00:13:40.980
Mochi is made to be a consumable object.

00:13:43.156 --> 00:13:46.278
I have no need for empty promises of mochi.

00:13:48.429 --> 00:13:49.983
Do you understand?

00:13:53.700 --> 00:13:55.579
Of...

00:13:56.469 --> 00:13:57.866
Of course...

00:13:58.916 --> 00:14:01.491
Of course, sir.

00:14:04.643 --> 00:14:06.487
You joking around?

00:14:06.487 --> 00:14:08.626
I would never.

00:14:09.298 --> 00:14:12.238
Make sure you get me some delicious mochi.

00:14:13.620 --> 00:14:15.898
Don't you dare fail.

00:14:15.898 --> 00:14:17.905
Understood.

00:15:23.757 --> 00:15:27.080
It's fine. My salary
will be in the hundred millions.

00:15:27.080 --> 00:15:28.860
Go on and buy big.

00:15:28.860 --> 00:15:30.721
Yeah, later.

00:15:47.155 --> 00:15:48.601
Hello?

00:15:49.439 --> 00:15:51.354
Yeah, I'm headed home now.

00:15:52.116 --> 00:15:53.764
Are you okay?

00:15:55.984 --> 00:15:58.127
If you're hurting, tell me.

00:16:11.097 --> 00:16:12.541
Sorry.

00:16:15.778 --> 00:16:17.479
I know...

00:16:18.431 --> 00:16:21.967
I'm causing you trouble.

00:16:24.268 --> 00:16:26.353
I know that, but...

00:16:29.401 --> 00:16:31.306
I just, I want to...

00:16:35.361 --> 00:16:38.913
No, never mind.

00:16:39.859 --> 00:16:42.863
I'll buy us some meat on the way home.

00:16:43.947 --> 00:16:45.497
Talk to you soon.

00:17:24.327 --> 00:17:26.482
I knew I'd find you here.

00:17:31.977 --> 00:17:34.455
Akito contacted me.

00:17:58.673 --> 00:18:00.817
I was fired.

00:18:01.923 --> 00:18:04.071
Akito filled me in.

00:18:09.213 --> 00:18:12.303
Coming here won't bring any of it back.

00:18:13.036 --> 00:18:15.125
Not her.

00:18:15.719 --> 00:18:17.852
Not us.

00:18:22.460 --> 00:18:24.225
I'm sorry.

00:18:24.225 --> 00:18:26.617
Oh, stop it.

00:18:27.234 --> 00:18:30.849
I've seen enough of you blaming yourself.

00:18:31.509 --> 00:18:34.703
It's time we both move on.

00:18:39.035 --> 00:18:42.345
This is not where you belong right now.

00:18:44.332 --> 00:18:46.755
You can't win baseball on your own.

00:18:50.181 --> 00:18:52.594
What matters is the team, right?

00:18:53.349 --> 00:18:55.764
Teams are where you share clashing opinions.

00:18:55.764 --> 00:18:58.306
Where you can be true to yourself.

00:18:58.306 --> 00:19:02.218
Where you can share both joys and sorrows.

00:19:05.972 --> 00:19:09.347
I know you want to protect that team.

00:19:10.634 --> 00:19:13.163
But the team wants to protect you, too.

00:19:20.285 --> 00:19:22.462
What? Did I say something strange?

00:19:22.462 --> 00:19:23.896
No.

00:19:23.896 --> 00:19:26.292
You know nothing about baseball, do you?

00:19:26.292 --> 00:19:27.604
Hey!

00:19:27.604 --> 00:19:31.263
This is what sports are all about.

00:19:32.042 --> 00:19:33.584
Am I wrong?

00:19:36.200 --> 00:19:37.796
Thank you.

00:19:47.123 --> 00:19:52.537
If it's not a fair assessment,
we have no intention of signing.

00:19:52.537 --> 00:19:54.083
Our assessment is entirely fair.

00:19:54.083 --> 00:19:56.966
You let a complete amateur do the work.

00:19:58.729 --> 00:20:00.989
You're practically scamming us.

00:20:00.989 --> 00:20:03.670
He was not hired through connections.

00:20:03.670 --> 00:20:07.893
We determined he was an irreplaceable asset,
and offered him the role.

00:20:11.323 --> 00:20:15.233
My name is Akito Sakurazaki,
of the Data Analytics Team.

00:20:15.233 --> 00:20:18.311
Please allow me to explain
our criteria for this assessment.

00:20:21.904 --> 00:20:23.826
Hey, Iwata.

00:20:25.010 --> 00:20:28.091
Leave the negotiations with the GM to me.

00:20:28.091 --> 00:20:29.585
Let's go.

00:20:30.287 --> 00:20:31.550
Right.

00:20:37.505 --> 00:20:41.812
First, I admit that your salaries
are below the market average.

00:20:42.518 --> 00:20:43.910
See?

00:20:43.910 --> 00:20:47.050
Our team's financial situation is to blame.

00:20:47.050 --> 00:20:48.278
We're sorry we cannot do more.

00:20:48.278 --> 00:20:49.796
Are you kidding me?

00:20:49.796 --> 00:20:51.985
Don't think that's a valid excuse.

00:20:51.985 --> 00:20:57.410
Still, these contracts
are favorable for you all.

00:20:57.934 --> 00:20:58.979
Huh?

00:20:58.979 --> 00:21:00.971
Mr. Shirasaki.

00:21:02.261 --> 00:21:04.388
Your batting average is a .214.

00:21:04.388 --> 00:21:07.075
Your stolen base success rate is 50%.

00:21:07.075 --> 00:21:09.850
These stats are comparable
to batters in the minor leagues.

00:21:09.850 --> 00:21:11.406
What?

00:21:11.406 --> 00:21:13.307
Why's everyone such a harsh critic?

00:21:13.307 --> 00:21:14.795
Mr. Shirasaki.

00:21:14.795 --> 00:21:16.720
There's more.

00:21:19.138 --> 00:21:21.601
However, your batted balls
have great velocity.

00:21:21.601 --> 00:21:24.278
Your average batted velocity

00:21:24.278 --> 00:21:26.824
ranks within the top 15%
of the entire league.

00:21:26.824 --> 00:21:28.847
If you continue to step up to plate,

00:21:28.847 --> 00:21:32.687
you could make a name for yourself
as a home run hitter.

00:21:32.687 --> 00:21:35.490
What? Is that a compliment?

00:21:35.490 --> 00:21:36.936
You ought to offer me more!

00:21:36.936 --> 00:21:41.563
But this is only if you continue to bat.

00:21:42.970 --> 00:21:44.248
Given your current stats,

00:21:44.248 --> 00:21:47.534
other teams would barely put you in play.

00:21:48.540 --> 00:21:51.196
But with Tatsuya Kudo gone,

00:21:51.196 --> 00:21:53.885
the Dreams are short on home run hitters.

00:21:53.885 --> 00:21:57.119
You would play at least 100 games with us.

00:21:57.119 --> 00:22:01.005
That's about 4.37 times more often
than if you played with another team.

00:22:05.126 --> 00:22:08.332
Yes, your salary next season will be low.

00:22:08.332 --> 00:22:11.020
But make a name for yourself next season,

00:22:11.020 --> 00:22:12.587
and a number of teams,

00:22:12.587 --> 00:22:16.146
including the Dreams,
will be writing you offers.

00:22:17.425 --> 00:22:20.127
Don't just look at the present.

00:22:20.127 --> 00:22:22.256
Look towards the future,

00:22:22.256 --> 00:22:25.205
and you'll realize this contract
isn't such a bad deal.

00:22:27.041 --> 00:22:31.343
Do you still believe his assessment
is the work of an amateur?

00:22:43.397 --> 00:22:46.991
I thought I was meeting the GM today.
What's going on?

00:22:46.991 --> 00:22:49.614
I am the current acting GM.

00:22:50.900 --> 00:22:53.963
So that amateur was fired after all.

00:22:53.963 --> 00:22:56.520
Are the Dreams going to be okay?

00:22:57.068 --> 00:22:59.186
Don't be anxious.

00:22:59.186 --> 00:23:00.844
Likewise.

00:23:01.993 --> 00:23:06.544
I hear Shirasaki's crew
rescinded their contracts?

00:23:06.544 --> 00:23:09.313
Not to worry. It's been taken care of.

00:23:09.313 --> 00:23:10.610
That so.

00:23:10.610 --> 00:23:13.387
Iwata is the only one left.

00:23:14.736 --> 00:23:18.555
All I ask for is a fair evaluation.

00:23:18.555 --> 00:23:22.037
And don't try offering him
a meager 60 million again.

00:23:22.037 --> 00:23:26.128
Of course.
We have re-evaluated our negotiation.

00:23:32.207 --> 00:23:34.717
[74 million yen]

00:23:36.391 --> 00:23:37.787
Hey.

00:23:40.679 --> 00:23:43.275
Are you serious about signing with me?

00:23:44.708 --> 00:23:47.500
Given the average rate
amongst other professionals,

00:23:47.500 --> 00:23:49.940
our analyst has estimated
your average salary to be

00:23:49.940 --> 00:23:52.577
around 70 million yen this season.

00:23:52.577 --> 00:23:55.197
[League estimate: 70 million yen]

00:23:55.197 --> 00:23:58.338
An assessment done by an amateur, I take it.

00:23:58.338 --> 00:24:00.968
Are you aware of the blog, "Banzai Baseball"?

00:24:00.968 --> 00:24:05.096
It's quite famous, and relied upon
by many professional analysts.

00:24:05.096 --> 00:24:07.311
It is also run by our new hire.

00:24:09.327 --> 00:24:13.462
This is the most accurate assessment
a baseball analyst can offer.

00:24:13.462 --> 00:24:16.484
The most accurate assessment?

00:24:16.484 --> 00:24:19.195
Now you're being ridiculous.

00:24:19.195 --> 00:24:20.834
Offer me this little,

00:24:20.834 --> 00:24:25.139
and I'm taking the next season off for rehab.

00:24:26.755 --> 00:24:28.968
Know what I'm getting at?

00:24:29.670 --> 00:24:32.208
You'll be losing the catcher

00:24:32.208 --> 00:24:34.316
who can make the most of Sawada's pitches.

00:24:34.316 --> 00:24:38.323
You'd be throwing away your chance
to escape last place!

00:24:39.589 --> 00:24:41.381
I see.

00:24:41.381 --> 00:24:46.922
Does this mean
you see potential in our next season?

00:24:48.672 --> 00:24:50.267
So do I.

00:24:50.267 --> 00:24:53.104
I believe we can aim for victory next year.

00:24:53.104 --> 00:24:54.518
If we get the whole team, that is.

00:24:54.518 --> 00:24:55.712
Hey, now.

00:24:55.712 --> 00:24:58.766
Don't distract him with a dream.

00:24:58.766 --> 00:25:02.571
Professional baseball is a business.
It's no after-school club.

00:25:02.571 --> 00:25:07.256
If you want Iwata's power,
then make him a reasonable offer.

00:25:07.256 --> 00:25:09.954
That is why we're offering him
the average 70 million,

00:25:09.954 --> 00:25:12.042
with an additional 4 million
to express our expectations for him.

00:25:12.042 --> 00:25:16.160
Are you even listening to me?

00:25:18.429 --> 00:25:20.069
I understand.

00:25:20.999 --> 00:25:25.008
Iwata is an indispensable player
for the Dreams.

00:25:26.069 --> 00:25:31.942
I will offer an additional 8 million,
for an annual salary of 82 million yen.

00:25:38.977 --> 00:25:41.027
[82 million yen]

00:25:49.148 --> 00:25:55.340
Raising someone's salary
means lowering someone else's.

00:25:58.102 --> 00:25:59.834
I'm sorry.

00:25:59.834 --> 00:26:01.255
I know.

00:26:02.385 --> 00:26:05.934
I'm causing you trouble.

00:26:11.571 --> 00:26:15.110
That's why we negotiate
with all our might every day.

00:26:16.575 --> 00:26:20.516
Still, we cannot give up on you, Iwata.

00:26:21.198 --> 00:26:23.952
Even if that means offering less to others.

00:26:27.394 --> 00:26:31.227
Then do just that.

00:26:31.227 --> 00:26:33.473
Get him what he deserves!

00:26:33.473 --> 00:26:34.788
Isn't that right?

00:26:41.500 --> 00:26:45.472
I hope to be offered a fair price.

00:26:45.472 --> 00:26:47.116
Exactly.

00:26:47.116 --> 00:26:49.855
He's a candidate
for next year's Gold Glove Award.

00:26:49.855 --> 00:26:54.501
However, I missed most of the season
due to an injury.

00:26:55.126 --> 00:26:58.743
82 million is not fitting
for my performance this past season.

00:26:58.743 --> 00:27:00.970
Huh? What are you talking about?

00:27:00.970 --> 00:27:04.642
If I'm causing a player to be offered less,

00:27:04.642 --> 00:27:08.336
please give that person a fair evaluation.

00:27:08.336 --> 00:27:10.282
Hey, what are you talking about?

00:27:10.282 --> 00:27:12.269
It's my contract!

00:27:12.269 --> 00:27:14.328
Let me do what I want.

00:27:16.247 --> 00:27:20.321
We, the Dreams, are a team.

00:27:27.821 --> 00:27:29.526
Hey. Iwata!

00:27:29.526 --> 00:27:30.772
[74 million yen]

00:27:30.772 --> 00:27:32.545
Iwata.

00:27:34.114 --> 00:27:35.552
Iwata!

00:27:35.552 --> 00:27:40.172
Mr. Kurokawa. You're no longer
involved with the Dreams, are you?

00:27:42.314 --> 00:27:43.939
Please leave.

00:28:01.600 --> 00:28:03.801
I'm sorry.

00:28:03.801 --> 00:28:05.211
For a lot of things.

00:28:08.654 --> 00:28:11.871
I'll barely forgive you.

00:28:14.428 --> 00:28:15.805
Though, well...

00:28:16.670 --> 00:28:19.080
To make up for my signature,

00:28:20.962 --> 00:28:23.070
I have a favor to ask.

00:28:25.673 --> 00:28:27.250
I already know.

00:28:29.575 --> 00:28:31.029
Welcome!

00:28:38.125 --> 00:28:39.596
Welcome.

00:28:40.576 --> 00:28:42.945
Here's your hot towel and water.

00:28:42.945 --> 00:28:45.619
Please call me when you're ready to order.

00:28:48.352 --> 00:28:50.332
I'm here to apologize today.

00:28:56.203 --> 00:29:00.008
I made an offer that was far below
your estimated worth.

00:29:02.372 --> 00:29:04.103
I'm truly sorry.

00:29:05.781 --> 00:29:07.065
No, well...

00:29:08.175 --> 00:29:09.934
Kijima.

00:29:11.545 --> 00:29:13.730
The Dreams need you.

00:29:17.866 --> 00:29:20.260
The team's critical financial situation...

00:29:22.163 --> 00:29:24.967
meant I could only offer you a meager amount.

00:29:27.179 --> 00:29:29.896
It was by no means a notice of dismissal.

00:29:33.397 --> 00:29:38.271
My own lack of power is blame.

00:29:42.661 --> 00:29:48.003
I'm so, truly sorry.

00:29:55.759 --> 00:29:57.445
You've left the team.

00:29:58.465 --> 00:30:01.194
Why go out of your way to apologize?

00:30:05.283 --> 00:30:07.142
Because this is the truth.

00:30:09.297 --> 00:30:11.538
Something I couldn't express...

00:30:12.995 --> 00:30:14.933
while I worked as GM.

00:30:26.532 --> 00:30:30.566
Do you have any recommendations?

00:30:33.933 --> 00:30:35.754
Recommendations, you say...

00:30:36.587 --> 00:30:39.873
Our beef tongue and skirt steak
are my picks for the day.

00:30:41.399 --> 00:30:45.203
Then I'll have those.

00:30:45.203 --> 00:30:47.176
Sure thing.

00:30:47.176 --> 00:30:49.142
Good evening.

00:30:50.388 --> 00:30:52.596
Oh, GM!

00:30:59.888 --> 00:31:02.127
I've come with a new offer today.

00:31:02.127 --> 00:31:03.166
I told you, I'm no longer...

00:31:03.166 --> 00:31:05.499
No, I understand. I hear you.

00:31:05.499 --> 00:31:11.071
Which is why we offered Iwata your salary
as a bonus.

00:31:12.982 --> 00:31:17.151
But Iwata only had a message for you.

00:31:17.151 --> 00:31:22.338
He said,
"I still want to catch Kijima's pitches."

00:31:23.368 --> 00:31:26.649
He asked me to bring you back.

00:31:29.967 --> 00:31:31.417
Iwata did?

00:31:32.577 --> 00:31:33.836
Yes.

00:31:37.203 --> 00:31:39.073
Don't worry.

00:31:39.073 --> 00:31:42.128
I'm ready to catch your pitches next season.

00:31:55.023 --> 00:31:56.771
Mr. Kijima...

00:32:04.284 --> 00:32:06.644
Can I go grab a pen?

00:32:11.317 --> 00:32:12.792
Of course.

00:32:27.518 --> 00:32:29.128
GM!

00:32:29.128 --> 00:32:30.817
We did it!

00:32:37.530 --> 00:32:38.807
GM?

00:32:39.902 --> 00:32:42.681
We didn't lose a single player.

00:32:42.681 --> 00:32:44.129
Yup!

00:32:44.129 --> 00:32:45.848
Everyone has been signed on!

00:32:45.848 --> 00:32:48.161
Yes!

00:32:48.161 --> 00:32:50.288
Alright! I'm treating today!

00:32:50.288 --> 00:32:52.894
Don't get cocky
just because your family is rich.

00:32:52.894 --> 00:32:54.334
But today's a special occasion.

00:32:54.334 --> 00:32:56.378
People will keep saying
you got in through connections.

00:32:56.378 --> 00:32:58.782
- You're the only one who harps on that!
- Alright...

00:32:58.782 --> 00:33:01.550
Let's give it our all this winter,

00:33:01.550 --> 00:33:03.237
and make our next season a success!

00:33:03.237 --> 00:33:04.534
Cheers!

00:33:04.534 --> 00:33:07.298
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

00:33:11.085 --> 00:33:12.735
Good work.

00:33:13.443 --> 00:33:15.163
Likewise, sir.

00:33:17.698 --> 00:33:21.731
What? Did you want to treat us that badly?

00:33:21.731 --> 00:33:23.530
No, that's not it.

00:33:24.904 --> 00:33:26.658
But the GM isn't...

00:33:32.944 --> 00:33:34.384
Sorry.

00:33:38.377 --> 00:33:41.989
We've lost our key player, haven't we?

00:33:44.475 --> 00:33:46.312
On the GM's last day,

00:33:46.312 --> 00:33:48.838
I received the handover documents he made.

00:33:51.840 --> 00:33:53.935
There were so many documents.

00:33:55.025 --> 00:33:59.598
He must have spent hundreds of hours
researching everything about the Dreams.

00:34:00.374 --> 00:34:03.828
He said he had no attachment to the team.

00:34:03.828 --> 00:34:05.563
But I don't believe him for a second.

00:34:12.444 --> 00:34:13.890
I think my brother...

00:34:15.078 --> 00:34:18.041
is afraid of having
something important to him.

00:34:18.923 --> 00:34:20.353
Afraid?

00:34:21.757 --> 00:34:24.491
He doesn't want to suffer loss ever again.

00:34:25.810 --> 00:34:29.426
That's why he doesn't save
anyone's contact info.

00:34:34.024 --> 00:34:36.077
When I got hurt,

00:34:37.502 --> 00:34:40.014
my brother lost his family, too.

00:34:45.281 --> 00:34:47.114
That's enough!

00:34:47.114 --> 00:34:48.931
What happened to Akito is not your fault.

00:34:48.931 --> 00:34:51.303
If I had been a bit more perceptive...

00:34:51.303 --> 00:34:53.269
If I hadn't said those things,
none of this would've happened!

00:34:53.269 --> 00:34:55.967
Enough with the "ifs" and the self-blame!

00:34:55.967 --> 00:34:59.114
Are we not allowed to move on?

00:34:59.114 --> 00:35:01.147
Well, are we?

00:35:04.842 --> 00:35:06.126
Ouch.

00:35:07.033 --> 00:35:08.925
- Ouch.
- Sawako?

00:35:08.925 --> 00:35:10.700
Sawako! Sawako!

00:35:10.700 --> 00:35:12.425
Hey.

00:35:12.425 --> 00:35:14.092
Are you okay?

00:35:14.092 --> 00:35:15.792
Sawako!

00:35:17.399 --> 00:35:18.912
My brother...

00:35:24.793 --> 00:35:27.517
continued to blame himself.

00:35:27.517 --> 00:35:29.981
He felt responsible for everything.

00:35:37.100 --> 00:35:39.374
Unable to focus on work anymore,

00:35:41.523 --> 00:35:44.328
he was transferred to a hockey team
on the verge of disbanding.

00:35:46.339 --> 00:35:49.232
My brother eventually filed his divorce,

00:35:49.232 --> 00:35:51.561
and began working solely for my sake.

00:35:53.418 --> 00:35:56.052
Though he led that hockey team to victory,

00:35:56.052 --> 00:35:58.468
they ultimately disbanded after a year.

00:35:59.279 --> 00:36:02.888
Afterwards, he drifted aimlessly
from sport to sport.

00:36:04.856 --> 00:36:07.852
No one protected him.

00:36:10.989 --> 00:36:14.926
I think my brother
is beginning to care about the Dreams.

00:36:15.550 --> 00:36:16.545
So...

00:36:16.545 --> 00:36:18.511
He's blaming himself again.

00:36:18.511 --> 00:36:20.050
What?

00:36:20.050 --> 00:36:22.000
To quote the GM directly,

00:36:22.000 --> 00:36:26.421
he said these negotiations hurt the players,

00:36:26.421 --> 00:36:28.827
and destroyed the team.

00:36:34.048 --> 00:36:36.335
- That doesn't sit right with me.
- Huh?

00:36:37.193 --> 00:36:39.909
We ought to do the protecting, too.

00:36:39.909 --> 00:36:41.270
Right?

00:36:42.265 --> 00:36:44.407
Maybe it's not too late.

00:36:45.216 --> 00:36:48.359
Let's protect the GM, together.

00:36:49.108 --> 00:36:50.619
Yes, ma'am!

00:37:09.525 --> 00:37:13.093
I've arranged this press conference today

00:37:13.093 --> 00:37:16.145
to explain our decision
in hiring our GM's brother.

00:37:17.516 --> 00:37:22.472
First, we only discovered they were brothers
after the interview.

00:37:25.772 --> 00:37:30.051
The GM gave his brother the lowest score.

00:37:32.368 --> 00:37:37.197
While myself and Analytics Director Inamura,
gave him full marks.

00:37:38.089 --> 00:37:41.893
Though we hired the applicant
with the highest total score,

00:37:41.893 --> 00:37:45.353
we understand this caused a misunderstanding.

00:37:46.035 --> 00:37:49.729
However, Akito Sakurazaki is actually...

00:37:51.840 --> 00:37:55.242
What was that press conference?

00:37:56.820 --> 00:37:59.473
It was a means
to restore the team's credibility.

00:37:59.473 --> 00:38:00.849
What?

00:38:00.849 --> 00:38:05.484
Our upcoming announcement of
the GM's resignation would have sufficed.

00:38:05.484 --> 00:38:08.917
It was more important to reveal the truth.

00:38:10.130 --> 00:38:13.944
Our negotiations with Iwata
have also come to a close.

00:38:14.571 --> 00:38:18.731
Is there any reason to fire the GM now?

00:38:51.048 --> 00:38:52.500
Yes?

00:38:52.500 --> 00:38:54.281
Breaking news.

00:38:54.281 --> 00:38:57.902
Akito's suspicions
have been completely cleared.

00:38:57.902 --> 00:39:01.912
[Dreams Analyst was the famed "Robinson"!]

00:39:02.616 --> 00:39:05.080
Did you suddenly become a reporter?

00:39:05.080 --> 00:39:07.955
A smile would do, you know.

00:39:07.955 --> 00:39:12.207
No more taking all the blame yourself.

00:39:13.415 --> 00:39:18.055
Please come back to the Dreams.

00:39:21.019 --> 00:39:23.394
My salary has already been guaranteed.

00:39:24.572 --> 00:39:29.419
Why should I return to a last-place team now?

00:39:29.419 --> 00:39:32.397
Again with the cold attitude.

00:39:33.302 --> 00:39:36.252
I'm sure you already know why.

00:39:41.234 --> 00:39:46.693
The Dreams were never allowed to be dreamers.

00:39:47.914 --> 00:39:51.125
No one protected the team, after all.

00:39:52.580 --> 00:39:54.570
But now, things are different.

00:39:55.422 --> 00:39:58.591
The Dreams have you.

00:40:02.879 --> 00:40:05.331
Let's protect the team, together.

00:40:09.010 --> 00:40:11.611
We're not alone.

00:40:11.611 --> 00:40:15.399
Mr. Inamura joined me
at the press conference.

00:40:15.399 --> 00:40:18.945
This article was written
by PR Director Suzumori.

00:40:19.779 --> 00:40:22.371
Even Miyahara worked his butt off.

00:40:24.150 --> 00:40:28.969
Akito cleared his name with his own efforts.

00:40:35.103 --> 00:40:37.168
President Negishi once told me...

00:40:38.877 --> 00:40:43.183
that in an organization,
you can't stick to your beliefs.

00:40:46.313 --> 00:40:53.381
But I believe with the right people,
it's entirely possible.

00:41:01.351 --> 00:41:03.013
President Makita.

00:41:05.573 --> 00:41:08.352
I sent our player's into turmoil.

00:41:12.267 --> 00:41:14.356
So if I am to return,

00:41:15.736 --> 00:41:18.254
I wish to go back with a fight.

00:41:23.412 --> 00:41:25.583
Will you help me?

00:41:27.429 --> 00:41:28.781
Of course!

00:41:46.627 --> 00:41:48.317
Excuse me.

00:41:51.304 --> 00:41:52.747
What can I do for you?

00:41:52.747 --> 00:41:54.290
Isami.

00:41:54.290 --> 00:41:55.591
Yes.

00:41:55.591 --> 00:41:58.502
Here's a question.

00:42:00.621 --> 00:42:05.151
Is it difficult to have your subordinate's
servants carry your packages?

00:42:05.151 --> 00:42:06.877
Yes or no?

00:42:08.458 --> 00:42:10.175
No!

00:42:10.175 --> 00:42:11.442
In that case...

00:42:12.595 --> 00:42:16.137
What the hell is going on here?

00:42:16.830 --> 00:42:19.482
A servant's negligence
has the packages catching fire,

00:42:19.482 --> 00:42:20.917
and now my house is burning down!

00:42:20.917 --> 00:42:22.302
[Can the Dreams not afford their GM?]

00:42:22.302 --> 00:42:24.222
[The Yaoshima Group, in dire straits?]

00:42:25.112 --> 00:42:26.820
Sir.

00:42:26.820 --> 00:42:28.534
These are all false reports.

00:42:28.534 --> 00:42:30.364
False reports?

00:42:30.364 --> 00:42:34.657
Who could have manipulated
all this information?

00:42:36.378 --> 00:42:38.408
I told you, didn't I?

00:42:38.408 --> 00:42:43.139
I have no need for empty promises of mochi.

00:42:44.800 --> 00:42:47.045
Yet our stock is plummeting,

00:42:47.045 --> 00:42:49.892
and my entire Group is suffering huge losses!

00:42:49.892 --> 00:42:51.939
How do you explain that?

00:42:52.636 --> 00:42:55.351
Who did this!

00:42:55.351 --> 00:42:57.648
I will deal with it immediately.

00:42:57.648 --> 00:42:59.022
You'd better.

00:42:59.022 --> 00:43:01.007
You have until day's end.

00:43:01.007 --> 00:43:02.717
Hurry up!

00:43:03.907 --> 00:43:05.628
Yes, sir.

00:43:14.849 --> 00:43:17.006
Now, now, now, now.

00:43:17.540 --> 00:43:20.306
Relax.

00:43:24.232 --> 00:43:26.883
Hang in there, yeah?

00:43:26.883 --> 00:43:29.076
At least until I take over.

00:43:30.320 --> 00:43:31.473
Hey.

00:43:31.473 --> 00:43:32.873
Why are you dawdling?

00:43:32.873 --> 00:43:35.598
You've got a fire to put out. Go on.

00:43:35.598 --> 00:43:37.726
Hurry up!

00:43:39.493 --> 00:43:45.267
I can't think of anyone else
who could spread such an article.

00:43:46.776 --> 00:43:48.994
What do you think you're doing?

00:43:48.994 --> 00:43:53.248
I told you I'd guarantee your salary!

00:43:54.268 --> 00:43:59.248
It seems the reporter misunderstood
my statement regarding "budget cuts".

00:43:59.248 --> 00:44:03.110
Enough fooling around.

00:44:03.110 --> 00:44:07.988
Do you realize how much our shareholders lost
because of your shallow prank?

00:44:09.966 --> 00:44:12.311
I wouldn't know. 30 percent?

00:44:14.117 --> 00:44:16.732
That is not funny.

00:44:19.044 --> 00:44:22.388
Stocks are only down 9%.

00:44:22.388 --> 00:44:26.332
The players suffered a 30% cut.

00:44:26.332 --> 00:44:29.369
Watch your mouth!

00:44:32.471 --> 00:44:34.843
I'll withdraw your dismissal as GM,

00:44:34.843 --> 00:44:37.134
so quickly retract the article.

00:44:37.134 --> 00:44:39.797
My brother's allegedly "suspicious" hire,

00:44:40.380 --> 00:44:44.889
and our salary negotiation issues
have all been resolved.

00:44:44.889 --> 00:44:47.595
Regardless of what you say,

00:44:47.595 --> 00:44:49.757
I no longer have any reason to quit as GM.

00:44:49.757 --> 00:44:52.343
Then what is it you want?

00:44:52.343 --> 00:44:55.515
If you're so concerned about the 9% drop,

00:44:55.515 --> 00:44:57.823
then raise our total salary budget.

00:44:58.465 --> 00:45:02.287
Those cuts are why the group
looks financially unstable.

00:45:02.287 --> 00:45:06.613
Fine, I'll give you that paltry sum.
Now retract the article!

00:45:08.587 --> 00:45:10.026
What did you just say?

00:45:10.026 --> 00:45:11.487
Huh?

00:45:11.487 --> 00:45:14.289
Do you realize your "paltry sum"...

00:45:14.863 --> 00:45:19.643
had the staff and players
at each other's necks?

00:45:21.149 --> 00:45:23.190
I suggest you give that some thought.

00:45:32.303 --> 00:45:35.711
Why do you refuse to obey me?

00:45:39.568 --> 00:45:41.909
Will obeying orders change anything?

00:45:44.303 --> 00:45:48.326
In my experience, it never does.

00:45:53.264 --> 00:45:55.222
Do your experiences prove me wrong?

00:46:40.143 --> 00:46:42.973
[Fukumoto]

00:46:48.811 --> 00:46:50.711
So, the GM.

00:46:50.711 --> 00:46:52.213
What happened to him?

00:46:52.213 --> 00:46:53.923
I'll fill you in later.

00:46:53.923 --> 00:46:57.285
We have negotiations to redo.

00:46:57.285 --> 00:46:58.594
Huh?

00:46:59.784 --> 00:47:01.330
Excuse me.

00:47:02.633 --> 00:47:04.225
Good afternoon.

00:47:04.225 --> 00:47:06.515
- Good afternoon.
- Good afternoon.

00:47:07.737 --> 00:47:09.021
Have a seat.

00:47:12.577 --> 00:47:15.292
Your contract has been modified.

00:47:15.292 --> 00:47:17.204
Please look over our revisions.

00:47:21.518 --> 00:47:23.873
[34.5 million yen]

00:47:23.873 --> 00:47:25.313
What?

00:47:25.313 --> 00:47:28.665
It's a 15% increase.

00:47:30.216 --> 00:47:32.124
Thank you.

00:47:49.897 --> 00:47:52.127
[12 million yen]

00:47:54.600 --> 00:47:57.208
We recognize it's a small increase, but...

00:47:57.208 --> 00:48:00.305
Oh, no. It helps a lot.

00:48:01.439 --> 00:48:03.326
But why?

00:48:03.326 --> 00:48:07.688
Mr. Sakurazaki went and negotiated
with the owner.

00:48:07.688 --> 00:48:13.620
He wanted the players' true values
to be recognized.

00:48:13.620 --> 00:48:15.952
- The GM did?
- Yes!

00:48:21.252 --> 00:48:23.300
Thank you very much.

00:48:23.300 --> 00:48:24.894
Here's to another year!

00:48:24.894 --> 00:48:26.038
- The pleasure's mine.
- Thank you.

00:48:26.038 --> 00:48:28.004
Alright!

00:48:29.217 --> 00:48:35.287
[Signature - Yuki Kijima]

00:48:45.883 --> 00:48:47.247
Hey, Kijima!

00:48:47.247 --> 00:48:48.720
Oh, Iwata!

00:48:50.464 --> 00:48:51.788
Listen...

00:48:51.788 --> 00:48:53.252
It didn't work at all.

00:48:53.252 --> 00:48:54.168
Huh?

00:48:54.168 --> 00:48:57.609
My plan to threaten staff for big bucks.

00:48:57.609 --> 00:49:00.145
You're a real menace, you know that?

00:49:00.145 --> 00:49:04.522
Instead, I'm going to make a fortune
winning the series next season.

00:49:04.522 --> 00:49:06.180
You in?

00:49:06.180 --> 00:49:08.279
Yeah...

00:49:08.279 --> 00:49:09.429
You've got a deal!

00:49:09.429 --> 00:49:10.629
Woah there!

00:49:10.629 --> 00:49:11.742
Here he comes!

00:49:11.742 --> 00:49:14.425
- Go, go, go!
- You weigh nothing.

00:49:15.064 --> 00:49:18.151
Count me in for next season!

00:49:18.151 --> 00:49:19.749
Alright!

00:49:19.749 --> 00:49:21.623
Get him!

00:49:23.180 --> 00:49:24.978
Stop it!

00:49:24.978 --> 00:49:27.476
I don't have my shoes today!

00:50:00.442 --> 00:50:02.536
Don't get antsy, folks.

00:50:03.900 --> 00:50:06.930
- We're just early.
- Right, right.

00:50:06.930 --> 00:50:08.511
He's here, he's here!

00:50:08.511 --> 00:50:10.579
And he turned the corner.

00:50:10.579 --> 00:50:11.642
Hey!

00:50:11.642 --> 00:50:13.442
Never mind, here he comes!

00:50:13.442 --> 00:50:15.256
Get ready! Everyone ready?

00:50:15.256 --> 00:50:16.759
Ready?

00:50:19.992 --> 00:50:22.331
Welcome back!

00:50:22.331 --> 00:50:27.138
Our GM has returned!

00:50:28.682 --> 00:50:30.155
GM.

00:50:40.026 --> 00:50:44.028
And if I may add,
I went and bought the cake.

00:50:46.176 --> 00:50:47.505
Huh?

00:50:48.535 --> 00:50:49.539
Huh?

00:50:49.539 --> 00:50:52.259
Really? That's it?

00:50:52.259 --> 00:50:57.160
Well, hey. At least he blew out his candles.

00:50:57.160 --> 00:50:59.386
He's going to shut himself in his room again.

00:50:59.386 --> 00:51:01.504
He's going to be immersed in work again.

00:51:01.504 --> 00:51:05.058
But we bought a cake! He's so cold-hearted.

00:51:05.058 --> 00:51:06.925
I'm sorry about him.

00:51:06.925 --> 00:51:10.821
If you're sorry,
finish the cake in his stead!

00:51:13.078 --> 00:51:14.348
That's right!

00:51:14.348 --> 00:51:15.913
Eat the whole thing!

00:51:15.913 --> 00:51:18.428
- The whole cake?
- Yeah, yeah.

00:51:19.138 --> 00:51:20.439
Come in.

00:51:21.845 --> 00:51:23.825
Excuse me.

00:51:29.853 --> 00:51:31.918
GM.

00:51:31.918 --> 00:51:34.595
We'll be holding
a welcome-back party for you tonight.

00:51:37.480 --> 00:51:38.907
I won't be there.

00:51:38.907 --> 00:51:41.326
But you're the guest of honor.

00:51:45.311 --> 00:51:46.848
Fine.

00:51:49.999 --> 00:51:51.695
President Makita.

00:51:53.353 --> 00:51:55.220
Yes.

00:51:55.220 --> 00:52:00.376
I am here today thanks to all of you.

00:52:03.081 --> 00:52:05.925
Please tell them I'm grateful.

00:52:09.744 --> 00:52:11.468
Okay.

00:52:11.468 --> 00:52:13.499
I will definitely tell them.

00:52:15.783 --> 00:52:18.178
You should have started with that.

00:52:18.178 --> 00:52:20.449
Actually, why not tell them yourself?

00:52:23.381 --> 00:52:25.104
I'll think about it.

00:52:27.921 --> 00:52:29.589
Then if you'll excuse me.

00:52:32.692 --> 00:52:35.626
Our player roster for the season
has finally been solidified.

00:52:35.626 --> 00:52:38.059
What a harrowing negotiation period.

00:52:38.059 --> 00:52:40.138
Now we can fully prepare for camp.

00:52:40.138 --> 00:52:42.179
Alright!

00:52:44.521 --> 00:52:49.141
I will announce our potential camping sites.

00:52:49.910 --> 00:52:52.647
I'm betting on Okinawa.

00:53:06.957 --> 00:53:09.117
[Mom]

00:53:17.070 --> 00:53:18.690
Yes, what is it?

00:53:19.304 --> 00:53:20.935
Huh?

00:53:20.935 --> 00:53:22.389
What do you mean?

00:53:22.389 --> 00:53:26.361
Why does Dad have to fix someone else's roof?

00:53:26.361 --> 00:53:28.383
Oh, I see.

00:53:28.383 --> 00:53:32.745
Why do you only call in dire situations?

00:53:32.745 --> 00:53:35.482
Give me a break!

00:53:35.482 --> 00:53:38.820
Okay, okay. I'll wire you the money.

00:53:38.820 --> 00:53:40.178
Bye.

00:54:07.294 --> 00:54:09.664
[Ryuta]

00:54:18.052 --> 00:54:19.299
Did you hear that?

00:54:19.299 --> 00:54:21.312
- Don't be stupid.
- No, seriously. Did you?

00:54:21.312 --> 00:54:23.668
There's no way I'd say it first.

00:54:23.668 --> 00:54:25.480
Unbelievable.

00:54:25.480 --> 00:54:28.042
That's not fair. I said it first, didn't I?

00:54:28.042 --> 00:54:32.110
Hey, we've been waiting for you.

00:54:32.110 --> 00:54:34.253
Sorry to keep you waiting.

00:54:36.289 --> 00:54:38.689
Here, have a drink.

00:54:38.689 --> 00:54:40.764
You're wasted.

00:54:40.764 --> 00:54:41.610
Thank you.

00:54:41.610 --> 00:54:44.550
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

00:54:45.270 --> 00:54:47.317
I heard you're interested in medicine.

00:54:47.317 --> 00:54:51.301
My uncle's a medical man himself.
I'll introduce you next time.

00:54:51.301 --> 00:54:53.110
Yes?

00:54:53.110 --> 00:54:55.857
Oh, please do.

00:54:55.857 --> 00:55:00.275
But why medicine?
Is someone in your family a doctor?

00:55:00.275 --> 00:55:02.803
No. Not exactly.

00:55:02.803 --> 00:55:06.311
Hey. His dad is unemployed.

00:55:06.311 --> 00:55:08.817
I just told you.

00:55:08.817 --> 00:55:10.189
Shut up!

00:55:10.753 --> 00:55:13.902
Oh, my apologies.

00:55:15.649 --> 00:55:18.549
But until a while ago,

00:55:18.549 --> 00:55:21.388
he used to do work changing light bulbs.

00:55:21.388 --> 00:55:24.850
But seriously, what kind of job is that?

00:55:24.850 --> 00:55:26.063
- Changing light bulbs?
- I wouldn't know.

00:55:26.063 --> 00:55:27.621
- Never seen that before.
- Never even heard of it!

00:55:27.621 --> 00:55:31.190
Anyway, this guy was done in
by his own subordinate.

00:55:31.190 --> 00:55:34.208
He dropped our stocks by 9%.

00:55:34.208 --> 00:55:36.619
Nine percent!

00:55:37.421 --> 00:55:41.508
Just between you and me,
this father and son?

00:55:42.125 --> 00:55:44.108
They're lacking here.

00:55:44.108 --> 00:55:47.300
Don't tell them though. It's our secret!

00:55:47.300 --> 00:55:50.134
So what? That was your fault?

00:55:50.134 --> 00:55:54.271
Come on, man. I lost money too.

00:55:54.271 --> 00:55:55.692
Alright, alright, alright.

00:55:55.692 --> 00:55:59.648
Isami said he'd pay up, yeah?

00:55:59.648 --> 00:56:01.833
- Oh, I see.
- That's right.

00:56:01.833 --> 00:56:03.455
It'll work out.

00:56:07.618 --> 00:56:10.343
Let's arm wrestle.

00:56:10.343 --> 00:56:12.087
You versus me.

00:56:12.087 --> 00:56:13.556
Huh?

00:56:13.556 --> 00:56:15.074
Come on.

00:56:15.939 --> 00:56:19.467
You think you can beat me in arm wrestling?

00:56:19.467 --> 00:56:21.751
Don't get cocky.

00:56:21.751 --> 00:56:23.809
Come on.

00:56:26.627 --> 00:56:30.459
Burning with rivalry against me?

00:56:30.459 --> 00:56:32.941
Don't get ahead of yourself!

00:56:32.941 --> 00:56:35.140
I'll be the referee.

00:56:35.140 --> 00:56:36.659
This'll be a piece of cake.

00:56:36.659 --> 00:56:37.968
Hey look.

00:56:37.968 --> 00:56:39.535
The perfect arena.

00:56:45.642 --> 00:56:47.338
Hold that for me.

00:56:49.288 --> 00:56:51.020
Alright, bring it.

00:56:51.020 --> 00:56:53.912
Ready, go!

00:56:55.904 --> 00:56:57.937
Go, go!

00:56:57.937 --> 00:56:59.795
What?

00:56:59.795 --> 00:57:01.654
Is that all you've got?

00:57:03.316 --> 00:57:04.148
What's wrong?

00:57:04.148 --> 00:57:05.668
- Hey, come on.
- What's wrong? What's wrong?

00:57:05.668 --> 00:57:06.878
Let me have it.

00:57:06.878 --> 00:57:09.096
You're going to lose!

00:57:09.096 --> 00:57:11.141
No way.

00:57:11.141 --> 00:57:13.758
He's so weak!

00:57:13.758 --> 00:57:15.455
- Seriously?
- Lame!

00:57:15.455 --> 00:57:17.757
Alright! It's over!

00:57:17.757 --> 00:57:19.150
Heave-ho!

00:57:21.942 --> 00:57:23.804
Hey!

00:57:23.804 --> 00:57:24.771
Wait a minute!

00:57:24.771 --> 00:57:27.390
Time, time! Give me a second!

00:57:29.183 --> 00:57:31.362
Damn it!

00:57:32.199 --> 00:57:33.874
Hey, let go!

00:57:34.414 --> 00:57:35.974
Let go of me!

00:57:44.756 --> 00:57:48.667
You're weak because you've never struggled
a damn day in your life!

00:57:56.572 --> 00:58:00.110
Quit disrespecting my father.

00:58:00.110 --> 00:58:02.574
He's also your uncle!